				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Ahh, so that's SWARM kiting<a name="52983"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 9:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hey all.  I finally figured out swarm kiting.
<br />

<br />
I just went from 55.00 to 56.50 in 3 hours in PoN on Nightstalkers.  
<br />

<br />
I cannot believe how easy swarming is once you get the hang of it. I think I was thrown off by the name, &quot;Swarm&quot; kiting. I read every guide on this awesome website and read through a bunch of posts about swarm kiting but I think I had a mental block over what it really meant. I kept seeing swarm and thought somehow I got all the mobs to attack each other?... all at the same time? You know.. like a SWARM.. lol..? I know.. sometimes I'm dense that way... LOL.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, I read the guides again, went to PoN and camped the nightstalkers for 3 hours... AWESOME! I love it. XP at my level seemed to be a little over 1% per kill and I had it down to where I could break my charm and the ex-pet would have anywhere from 4% to 10% left.. I had 3 chants memmed and at 55 with TDoK they hit for 78 HPs then at 56 they landed for 81 HPs each.  The kill took no time at all.
<br />

<br />
I only have FT1 from my earring of the solstice and my mana pool isn't that great so I keep twisting my mana song in the middle of the kite. Other than that I keep snare up for when the last mob would wander and travel song mem'd to break the charm.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, all of you who write the guides are great! If I wasn't such a lunk-head, I would have figured this out earlier.. 
<br />

<br />
Oh well.. =)
<br />

<br />
Take care</span></td>
