			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ahh, so that's SWARM kiting<a name="53007"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 11:13 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Welcome to the party! Swarming is awesome, absolutely one of my favorite things to do in EQ, I'm glad you got the hang of it man. A few things that might help while you're polishing your skills:
<br />
   Replace that mana song with your snare song, as soon as you get down to the last one, it'll run like h*ll (assuming it's not undead) and you'll be glad you can stop it in time before it brings friends. 
<br />
   Get the gobbie ring in LoIO, the near instant invis helps hugely for timing and ease of control when breaking those charms. I know the camp is contested and kinda sucks in it's own way but anything worth getting will cause you some trouble, general rule of EQ. 
<br />
   I'm not trying to assume anything here but if you can afford it, get the ornate boots. I know they're a trifle expensive but trust me, they're totally worth the regen. It might also help you keep track of mana recovery better if you get a custom UI or setup the new numerical mana system in your regular UI. 
<br />
   The Hollowshade wars are incredibly easy to run and manipulate, although they do take some time to get the FT drop, it's another one that's very much worth it. All of the FT you get will be even more useful later when you get FM and start burning 900 mana per shot. 
<br />
   Two other things I found that helped. Make yourself a +int +mana gear set, put it on before you swarm and let your mana fill up while you chant kite or get some food or something. You can get as much as 400-500 extra mana for not that much money just switching out stuff for +mana +int gear. The other thing I wanted to say is that KEI helps. It <u>does not</u> regen any of your mana but it will boost your int, giving you a much larger mana pool, so IMO it's very necessary. 
<br />
   One more thing (sorry I'm getting carried away here) if you have Occlusion of Sound, mem it. Use it before you charm and it will save you a ton of mana by reducing those pesky resists. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, glad to see you're enjoying it, I hope these tidbits helped. 
<br />
Best of luck!
<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
