				<td colspan="2"><span>Wow.. some great information here! Thank you..
<br />

<br />
I didn't know my mana song or KEI didn't increase my mana regen.. bah.. what a bummer. I have FT1 as I said from my earring of the Solstice and I have been shopping for the Ornate boots for some time.  But they are going for 115K and 95K on BB right now.  I've seen them for 65K to 70K and I'm trying to hold out for that.
<br />

<br />
I do know about stat food and force feeding patty melts and fuzzlecutter so I dont eat my stat food.  My monk had one Tormentor Stir Fry for about 5 months.  My problem with stat food and forcefeeding is it takes up 4 slots in my inventory if I use both food and drink.  I currently have a custom UI that has a hotbutton window with my inventory slots showing around the outside.  It makes it a breeze to swap weapons for instruments when needed.
<br />

<br />
I suppose when swarming I really don't need to do too much swapping.. I keep my TDoK in my primary and switch to my Battle Drummers Main-Gauche when the last guy is running.  I could switch to stat food just for swarming.  Also, I do have the custom UI that shows my mana as a percentage.
<br />

<br />
The ring sounds like a good idea.  Is it castable from inventory? or do you need to equip? I suppose even equipped I could put it in a hotbutton, I have extra.  I have also thought about a mana suit of armor to wear when swarmming, I just haven't put one together yet. 
<br />

<br />
I am just depressed that my own mana song doesn't increase my mana regen..<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" /> and KEI doesn't help either? Is KEI that way for everyone? Does it just increase your mana pool to start? How do you increase mana regen other than with Flowing Thought items?
