				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ahh, so that's SWARM kiting<a name="53058"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 2:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The goblin ring is clickable from inventory as far as I know, but someone can correct me if I'm wrong here. You also have the option of doing the caller cycle with some friends and getting the cloak which I know for a fact is clickable from inv. I didn't see a magelo link, but it might not be a bad idea for you to do one, they're free and can tell you a lot about how different gear sets will affect your total mana pool size. Take a look at the cost of the charm song, then take a look at your pool and do some math in your head while you switch gear out, see what makes the most sense to you. For me, I used the arms from Hate, augmented with an int aug from LDoN, so I got about +16 from that, then I had a mask too, some arms and a head item that I switched out, all in all I got about 40 something int out of it, that's a good deal of extra mana, expecially when added to the bonus from KEI. As Shass pointed out, absolutely NOTHING will regen your mana besides FT items, AAs and Tribute bonuses, necros can't even twitch us, this is one of our bigger struggles that just gets even more important later in your bard life. She brought up a great point about tributes, use them whenever you can, anything you'd sell to a merchant, turn in for points and use them to get the extra regen, you'll be amazed at the difference. I also meant to mention that there are some FT augs in LDoN, the EF one isn't too hard to get but remember that you need gear with the proper slot to equip it.   </span></td>
