				<td colspan="2"><span>The war is definitly hard because of that stupid grimling being surrounded by greens and if u do get him down (which i did once) i then feel to the stupid defenders that summon.  The only thing i would suggest try is charming something and then sending it to the defenders as soon as the bears get there.
<br />

<br />
Also for the goblin ring it is only clickable from inventory (i just keep it perma equipped) there is a guide on the website so u dont have to constantly target urself and activate the ring.  It basically changes the target to u casts ring and changes back and u dont even notice anything happened (unless u try to switch target back then it appears as u instead of last mob)
<br />

<br />
As for the tribute points i did some investigating on my server (dont read the guide on tribute points in guide section it actually needs to be deleted and redone because the points are completly different now) But the best &quot;bang for ur buck&quot; point wise i saw was giving them a TDoK and buying a new one for around 3k which turned into about 2.24points/pp which isnt a bad tradeoff (the battleworn ch'ror used to be about 11 points/pp :(
<br />

<br />
At 56 u can only get that number for the FT up to 4 but w/ two FT slots (maybe 3 if u can get some people to help u do both the hollowshade war and grimling forest FT item) that can get ur Mana regen to 7.  If u do get boots at 60th level u will have a worn mana regen of 11/tick making u have a mana regen of 12/tick (does it go up some post 50/60? i dont know) which is real nice considering in 1 minute i will completely regen the mana needed to charm (which is about the amount of time it takes for the mob to die <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> )
<br />

<br />

<br />
Also when u hit 65 start doing some LDoNs (dont know for sure where the good plate armor is but do em there) The reason is the possibility of getting FT augs for ur armor (they are type  8 and for the life of me i cant remember what to do w/ those)</span></td>
