				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ahh, so that's SWARM kiting<a name="53737"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 26 04 9:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Swarming really dries up at 58 man, welcome to the fun grind of pushing 60 as fast as you can. I personally am a very casual player as of late, too much rl stuff to do so I haven't been on much but getting 59 was a huge pain in the a$ and 59-60 is going rediculously slow. Have you tried Nadox? I don't know how much you like grouping but now is the time to get into it if you want the good xp. PoV is the place to go, you can also chant kite there and in PoS as long as you don't go tagging some giant that summons you can make decent xp there if mindless chant kiting doesn't drive you insane. Once I got to this point I gave up on soloing, I just do it now while I LFG and even then it usually doesn't last long, I'd rather have hemmorhoids than run in another friggin cirlce <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" />
<br />
I've made way more friends, learned way more stuff about my class and had a h*ll of a lot more fun grouping, just do yourself a favor and stay away from LDoN. Usually around 58/59 you end up with a bunch of lvl 53-55 folks and get less than 4% for over an hour of time you'll never see again. On the other hand, once you reach 58 it means that you can do LDoNs with lvl 65 people. If you have any 65 friends, now is the time to bug them about helping you out because you can make some really good xp if you're the lowest in the group like that, just be sure to let them know you can't be reliable CC. And make sure to get Virtue before you go in   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />
Do you have your BoT key yet? At this point I really suggest trying to wrap little things like this up with high lvl friends while you suck up some good xp, it's really the best advice I can give since I'm only 59 myself and unless my rl hits the floor I'm not going to have enough time to grind it out to 60, at this point it really is just a huge time investment and a mental push, so don't give up!!
<br />
</span></td>
